    <note>Pan(1) Mei [1389] His father, Lin [3693], was a common soldier who advanced to a non-commissioned officer under Zhou Shizong and then served Song Zhao(1) Taizu [9001] as the general who pacified Guangnan. Zhao(1) Zhenzong's [9003] third empress was the daughter of Liu(2) Tong [17277], an officer, who served under Mei's command during the conquest of Guangnan. Liu(2) Tong's son was named Liu(2) Mei [3598]. Pan Mei's daughter was Zhao(1) Zhenzong's [9003] first empress. Mei was Su's [1390] granduncle, Zhang(1) Zhaoyun's [7149] and Cao(1) Wei's [8135] father-in-law, Zhang(1) Zhengzhong's [192] maternal grandfather, Zhang(1) Xiangzhong [226] was his wife's cousin. Guangdong TZ, 14.17a; SHY:ZG, 44.1b; SHY:SH, 49.3a-3b; SS, 258.14b; Du Dagui, 'xia,' 1.3b; YLDD, 12306.3b-4a. CBD, 5, 3628.</note>
